				<text_box font_color="#55AAFF" font_size="20pt" border_color="red" uid="416" x="3897.08" y="308.923" width="451" height="60.88">Light blue: parameter that should be calibrated or
can be used as policy/user input</text_box>
				<text_box uid="417" x="3898.37" y="401.587" width="366" height="196">Missing features / To-Dos: 
- Urbanisation/coastal migration
- There could be the option that dikes are not even maintained and then break down? Best to use this only when we actually account for well protected and badly protected areas.
- Should maintenance costs increase as sea level rises closer to the fp height?
- Higher fertility in low GDP unprotected coastal zones?</text_box>
