	</model>
	<model name="Coastal_population">
		<variables>
			<stock name="Coastal\npopulation" access="output" isee:autocreated="true">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
					<dim name="Coastal_Protection_level"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>Coastal_population_in_1980[Coastal_Protection_level]</eqn>
				<inflow>Population_growth_in_coastal_areas</inflow>
				<outflow>Annual_fatalities_due_to_coastal_floods</outflow>
				<outflow>People_retreating_from_the_coast</outflow>
				<units>Mp</units>
			</stock>
			<flow name="Population growth in\ncoastal areas">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
					<dim name="Coastal_Protection_level"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>Coastal_population[Run,Coastal_Protection_level]*population_growth_rate[1]</eqn>
				<units>Mp/year</units>
			</flow>
			<flow name="Annual fatalities due to\ncoastal floods">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
					<dim name="Coastal_Protection_level"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>Number_of_people_flooded_annually[Run,Coastal_Protection_level]*Fatality_rate_in_flood_events</eqn>
				<units>Mp/year</units>
			</flow>
			<flow name="People retreating from the coast" access="output" isee:autocreated="true">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
					<dim name="Coastal_Protection_level"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>Number_of_people_expectedly_flooded_in_50_years * Likelihood_that_expectedly_flooded_people_in_50_years_retreat_now[Run]
+
Number_of_people_flooded_annually * Retreat_rate_of_people_flooded_annually[Run]</eqn>
				<units>Mp/year</units>
			</flow>
			<aux name="Coastal\npopulation in 1980">
				<doc>575.6106582 Mp is the total population within the DIVA database</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Coastal_Protection_level"/>
				</dimensions>
				<element subscript="well_protected">
					<eqn>152</eqn>
				</element>
				<element subscript="insufficient">
					<eqn>228</eqn>
				</element>
				<units>Mp</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Number of\npeople flooded\nannually">
				<doc>If there is an improved distinction between protected/unprotected coastline, this should probably also be reworked.


Numbers from McMichael et al. (2020)
! WATCH OUT: Some number are for 1/100-year flood plains, other for 1/1000-year flood plains!

Hoozemans et al, 1993 (Book):
- 200-250 Mio. people live in 1/1000-year flood plain in 1990
- number increases by 50% for SLR of 1m, assuming no other change

Nicholls (2002):
- 10 Mio people flooded annually in 1990
- In 2100 this could be 83-510 Mio people annually (without flood protection)

Nicholls (2004):
- in 2080, 2-50 Mio people are additionally affected by flooding annually, depending on scenario
--&gt; Could check SLR in each scenario to create a number of people/metre...

Nicholls and Tol (2006):
-&gt; they also assume 200 Mio people living in the 1/1000-year coastal flood plain in 1990

Pardeans et al (2011):
-&gt; Without upgrading defences 84 Mio additional people are flooded annually in business-as-usual scenario

Vafeides et al. (2011):
- In 2000: 628 Mio people live in 1/100-year flood plain (?, Maybe this is rather the number for people in &quot;low elevation coastal zones&quot;, which often means coastal areas below 10 m above sea level)
- future increase is mostly because of migration towards the coast and less because of SLR

Jongman et al (2012):
- in 2010: 271 Mio people live in 1/100-year flood plain
- in 2050: 345 Mio people live in 1/100-year flood plain
--&gt; This might not consider climate change, i.e. SLR ?!

Hinkel et al. (2014);
- in 2100: 0.2-4.6% of world population will be flooded annually under 25-123 cm of GMSLR
- in 2100: 93-310 Mio people will live in the 1/100-year flood plain

Neumann et al. (2015):
- In 2000: 189 Mio people in 1/100-year flood plain
- In 2030: 282-285 Mio people ...
- In 2060: 315-411 Mio people

- In 2030: 879-949 Mio people in LECZ  (10.8-11.3%)
- In 2060: 1053-1388  Mio people in LECZ (11.8 - 13.3 %)

Muis et al. (2016):
- In 2000: 76 Mio people live in 1/100-year flood plain

Reimann et al. (2023):
- In 2000: 634 Mio people (10.3% of total population) live in LECZ, 360 Mio of this are urban areas (56.7%)
- In 2015: 815 Mio people (11.0%), 487 Mio urban (59.7%)
- In 2020: 898 Mio people (11.4%)</doc>
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
					<dim name="Coastal_Protection_level"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>(1-Flood_damage_resilience_in_unprotected_areas) * Flood_damage_function_for_people_in_coastal_areas * Coastal_population</eqn>
				<units>Mp/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Fatality rate\nin flood events">
				<doc>As in CIAM (Diaz, 2016, SI), based on Jonkman and Vrijling (2008)

Diaz, D. B. (2016). Estimating global damages from sea level rise with the Coastal Impact and Adaptation Model (CIAM). Climatic Change,
137(1–2), 143–156. https://doi.org/10.1007/s10584-016-1675-4

Jonkman S, Vrijling J (2008) Loss of life due to floods. Journal of Flood Risk Management 1(1):43–
56</doc>
				<eqn>0.01</eqn>
				<units>1</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Likelihood that expectedly flooded people in 50 years retreat now">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>0.01 * Retreat_switch</eqn>
				<units>1</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Retreat rate of people flooded annually">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>0.05*Retreat_switch</eqn>
				<units>1</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Expected global SLR\nin 50 years 1" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>metre</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="population growth rate" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>1/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Retreat switch" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>0.25 {0, 1}</eqn>
				<units>dmnl</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Flood damage resilience in unprotected areas" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
					<dim name="Coastal_Protection_level"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>1</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Flood damage function\nfor people in\ncoastal areas">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
					<dim name="Coastal_Protection_level"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>MIN(1, people_flood_damage_sensitivity* Flood_height_for_damage^people_flood_damage_elasticity)</eqn>
				<units>1/Year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="people flood damage\nsensitivity">
				<eqn>0.1</eqn>
				<units>1/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="people flood damage\nelasticity">
				<eqn>2.0</eqn>
				<units>dmnl</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Number of people\nexpectedly flooded\nin 50 years">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
					<dim name="Coastal_Protection_level"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>MIN(1, people_flood_damage_sensitivity * MAX(0,  (Expected_global_SLR_in_50_years_1[Run]+Effective_flood_height_1)/UNIT_metre) ^ people_flood_damage_elasticity)
* Coastal_population 
* (1 - Flood_damage_resilience_in_unprotected_areas)</eqn>
				<units>Mp/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Effective\nflood height 1" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
					<dim name="Coastal_Protection_level"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>metre</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Flood height for damage" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
					<dim name="Coastal_Protection_level"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>dmnl</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="UNIT metre">
				<eqn>1</eqn>
				<units>metre</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="global death rate from coastal flooding" access="output" isee:autocreated="true">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>Total_fatalities_due_to_coastal_floods/Population</eqn>
				<units>1/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Population" access="input">
				<dimensions>
					<dim name="Run"/>
				</dimensions>
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>Mp</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Total fatalities due to coastal floods" isee:derived_units="true">
				<eqn>SUM(Annual_fatalities_due_to_coastal_floods[*, well_protected]) + SUM(Annual_fatalities_due_to_coastal_floods[*, insufficient])</eqn>
				<isee:summing/>
				<units>Mp/year</units>
			</aux>
		</variables>
		<views>
			<style color="black" background="white" font_style="normal" font_weight="normal" text_decoration="none" text_align="center" vertical_text_align="center" font_color="black" font_family="Arial" font_size="10pt" padding="2" border_color="black" border_width="thin" border_style="none">
				<text_box color="black" background="white" text_align="left" vertical_text_align="top" font_size="12pt"/>
				<isee:loop_indicator color="black" background="white" text_align="left" vertical_text_align="top" font_size="12pt"/>
				<numeric_display color="white" background="white" font_size="12pt" border_width="thin" border_style="solid" isee:transparent="false" isee:show_divider="true" isee:show_bounding_box="true" label_side="left"/>
				<graph color="black" background="white" font_size="12pt" axis_color="#666666" grid_color="#C8C8C8" isee:graph_area_color="white" legend_position="bottom" isee:transparent="false" isee:hide_border="false" axis_title_font_style="normal" axis_title_font_weight="normal" axis_title_text_decoration="none" axis_title_text_align="center" axis_title_vertical_text_align="center" axis_title_font_color="black" axis_title_font_family="Arial" axis_title_font_size="12pt" axis_title_text_padding="2" axis_title_text_border_color="black" axis_title_text_border_width="thin" axis_title_text_border_style="none" axis_label_font_style="normal" axis_label_font_weight="normal" axis_label_text_decoration="none" axis_label_text_align="center" axis_label_vertical_text_align="center" axis_label_font_color="black" axis_label_font_family="Arial" axis_label_font_size="9pt" axis_label_text_padding="2" axis_label_text_border_color="black" axis_label_text_border_width="thin" axis_label_text_border_style="none">
					<isee:series_styles>
						<isee:series_style color="blue" thickness="1"/>
						<isee:series_style color="red" thickness="1" pen_style="dot_dashed"/>
						<isee:series_style color="fuchsia" thickness="1" pen_style="dotted"/>
						<isee:series_style color="#008F44" thickness="1" pen_style="dashed"/>
						<isee:series_style color="#FF7F00" thickness="1"/>
						<isee:series_style color="#7F00FF" thickness="1" pen_style="dot_dashed"/>
						<isee:series_style color="#0CA0FF" thickness="1" pen_style="dotted"/>
						<isee:series_style color="lime" thickness="1" pen_style="dashed"/>
						<isee:series_style color="#FF007F" thickness="1"/>
						<isee:series_style color="aqua" thickness="1" pen_style="dot_dashed"/>
						<isee:series_style color="#F586FF" thickness="1" pen_style="dotted"/>
						<isee:series_style color="black" thickness="1" pen_style="dashed"/>
						<isee:series_style color="#C8C8C8" thickness="1"/>
					</isee:series_styles>
				</graph>
				<table color="black" background="#E0E0E0" text_align="right" font_size="12pt" orientation="vertical" wrap_text="false" isee:auto_fit="true" isee:use_alternate_row_colors="false" isee:unlimited_table_length="false" blank_column_width="80" column_width="160" interval="1" report_balances="beginning" report_flows="instantaneous" header_font_style="normal" header_font_weight="normal" header_text_decoration="none" header_text_align="center" header_vertical_text_align="center" header_font_color="black" header_font_family="Arial" header_font_size="12pt" header_text_padding="2" header_text_border_color="black" header_text_border_width="thin" header_text_border_style="none"/>
